Commentary Text: Avesh Khan to Rohit, out Caught by Rabada!! It's been a brainfade phase for Rohit in this over. Even short and wide can be considered bait, if you're smart enough. He's kept him in check this over, and banged this in short, invites the cut, and Rohit throws his hands at the cut, gets a massive top-edge and Rabada comes around from third man to hold on to a regulation catch. Commentary Text: Bumrah to Hetmyer, out Caught by Rohit!! That's an absolute dolly and Bumrah has done what his skipper wanted him to do - was the slower off-cutter and Hetmyer didn't read it one bit - was early into the tuck as it was angled into his pads, closed the bat-face early and the ball gently lobbed to Rohit at short-cover, off the leading edge. That's a gift for the MI skipper and they've opened up DC's lower-order. Hetmyer c Rohit b Bumrah 15(8) [4s-2]

Once again the ball didn't bounce as much as he expected, struck on the back-thigh, but he was hanging back. No bat and UltraEdge confirms it - Umpire's call will be enough for MI and it indeed is - Axar is OUT. The indifferent Sharjah bounce has another casualty in Axar - short of a length and angling back into the left-hander, Axar saw the length and shaped for the pull, but the ball stood a tad low, skidded through and struck him bang in front of middle, was going on and crashing into the top of the stumps. Axar lbw b Boult 9(9) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Coulter-Nile to Smith, out Bowled!! The stumps are in a mess! Not a usual sight this - Smith being bowled around his legs. Sure, many bowlers dream of doing this on seeing his shuffling stance but don't think he has failed much to connect. It's a fellow Aussie who does the job this time. Coulter-Nile strikes first ball - probably a slower one and attacked the stumps. Smith was a tad early on the flick stroke after the shuffle across and exposed his leg pole a bit too much. Timber all over the place. DC in big trouble now. Smith b Coulter-Nile 9(8) [6s-1]

Commentary Text: Krunal Pandya to Prithvi Shaw, out Lbw!! Krunal deserves credit for this review! Rohit didn't seem that keen on the review but was coaxed into it by his spinner and boy, hasn't it worked! Smart bowling this, fired on a length with the stump-to-stump line, the lower bounce defeated Shaw's back foot pull and struck him on the back leg. Looked a marginal call in real time but as it turns out, HawkEye shows Three Reds and this is now a dream start for MI. Both openers back in the hut cheaply. Prithvi Shaw lbw b Krunal Pandya 6(7) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Jayant Yadav to Dhawan, out Dhawan Run Out!! Excellent stuff from Pollard! What were these two thinking while taking on his arm, that too from close range? So Dhawan charged down, got a shorter length that he knocked towards mid-on and wanted the single straightaway. Despite getting a headstart, he still isn't able to make it as Polly's throw hits the bulls-eye at the bowler's end. Looked gone in real time itself and replays confirm it. Huge wicket this, given the solidity Dhawan offers to the DC line-up. MI needed a spark of inspiration to kickstart the innings and they have got it. Dhawan run out (Pollard) 8(7) [6s-1]
